values:
Surprise PM visit

 

22 Sep 08 @ 10:58am by Alan Welburn

Kevin Rudd, baby Kardia Schacht, of Brighton, and Wayne Swan

CHERMSIDE: Prime Minister Kevin Rudd gave more than 140 families an extra treat at Chermside last Sunday.
Families from throughout the northside converged on 7th Brigade Park for the ninth Welcoming The Babies celebration, an initiative of Federal MP Wayne Swan.
Mums and dads proudly displayed their children, some of whom were newborns with at least four of them less than three weeks old.
The families were delighted to receive certifiicates and gifts to mark the occasion but were equally thrilled when Mr Rudd made an unexpected visit and shared the stage for the presentation before and after mingling with the families.
Mr Rudd said: “I am reliably informed more than 1200 babies have been welcomed at similar functions over the nine years Wayne has run this event.”
Mr Swan, the Federal MP for Lilley, said the event was a tribute to family pride and community and corporate support.
“Without the backing of our sponsors this event would not be achievable but it’s also dependant on all these northside families who are prepared to share this occasion with us,” Mr Swan said.
Mr Swan said the event would be held again next year. Read more in this week’s Northside Chronicle.

The Birth Story

I was having some slight pain on Sunday and felt more pressure than before so i had a funny feeling she was coming on Monday ...I woke up at around 2.30am Monday morning with contractions ...i work up Gerhard and said i think Kardia is coming today but go back to sleep i wake you when the contractions are closer i wasn't to sure if this was the real deal. (he doesn't remember me even doing this) .
i got up had a shower and sat down on the internet i had downloaded a program that times contractions i was having them about every 7-8 mins.
I had some rice bubbles and try to get back to sleep the pains weren't that bad...But enough to stop me from falling back to sleep so i went and had a bath and the contractions increased to about 5 mins apart ...Rang the hosptial at 5.30am and they said time to come in... i rang Aunty Sharon to say i got to drop Courtney off she was like i have to go to work today and i said um im going to have a baby today !! I woke up Gerhard and he was all excited...Woke Courtney she had the biggest smile on her face...left about 6am the contractions were picking up in the car and oh my god don't have a contraction going around a corner OUCH...so we basically threw Courtney out the car at Aunty Sharon's and got to the Redcliffe hospital at 6.30am ....
I was 7 cm dilated and the contractions were coming alot more closer and full on ... Kardia Erin Schacht was born at 7.36am...1 hour after i arrived at hospital.
She was 8 Pound 13 or 4.005kg
With a full head of black hair she looks just like her daddy :)

Just got to put the last rail on and its all done ...Daddy did a very nice job well done Daddy !!!
